  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-03-09",
    "date": "2021-07-12T18:17:29Z",
    "text": "Emergency Homelessness Assistance Act of 2021\n\nThis bill provides additional FY2021 funding for the Department of Housing and Urban Development's HOME Investment Partnerships Program. Funding is provided for tenant-based rental assistance, development and support of affordable housing, supportive housing services, and the acquisition of non-congregate shelter units. These units may remain non-congregate shelter units, be converted into permanent affordable housing, or be used as emergency shelter. Individuals qualifying for such assistance include at-risk veterans and individuals who are homeless, at risk of homelessness, or fleeing or attempting to flee domestic violence or other dangerous situations."
  },
